You have successfully built a production-ready resilient HTTP client library with:

Retry Logic: Automatically retries failed requests with configurable attempts
Exponential Backoff: Implements increasing delays between retries to avoid overwhelming services
Timeout Handling: Prevents indefinite waiting with configurable timeouts
Error Classification: Distinguishes between retryable and non-retryable errors
Circuit Breaker: Prevents cascading failures in distributed systems
